import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['state'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of zip codes across different states?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=90)
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    else:
        plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['latitude'], data['longitude'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitude and longitude values?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Latitude')
    plt.ylabel('Longitude')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    county_zip_counts = data.groupby('county')['zip_code'].count().sort_values(ascending=False)
    if len(county_zip_counts) > 20:
        county_zip_counts = county_zip_counts[:20]
    ax = county_zip_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    ax.set_xlabel('County')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Zip Codes')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of zip codes across different counties?', wrap=True)
    ax.xaxis.set_tick_params(rotation=90)
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
